# Sanity Token Guide

## What is a Sanity Token?
A Sanity token is a private API key that allows your application to authenticate with your Sanity project.

## Where to Find Your Sanity Token

1. Go to [https://www.sanity.io/manage](https://www.sanity.io/manage)
2. Select your project (k-are1)
3. Navigate to the "API" tab
4. Under "Tokens", click "Create new token"
5. Give it a name (e.g., "Development" or "Production")
6. Select appropriate permissions (typically "Read" for frontend apps, "Write" if needed)
7. Click "Create token"
8. Copy the generated token value

## Setting Up Your Token

1. Create a `.env` file in your project root if it doesn't exist
2. Add your token as:
   ```
   VITE_SANITY_API_TOKEN=your_sanity_token_here
   ```
3. Make sure `.env` is in your `.gitignore` to keep the token secure

The token is accessed in [src/lib/sanity.ts](mdc:src/lib/sanity.ts) using `import.meta.env.VITE_SANITY_API_TOKEN`.

Remember: Never commit your Sanity token to version control!
